.TH PRINTF 1 "November 2023" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
.B printf
\- format and print data

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B printf FORMAT [ARGUMENT]...

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B printf
formats and prints data according to the FORMAT specification. It is similar to the C
function \fIprintf()\fR and provides a powerful way to format and display output.

.SH OPTIONS
The \fBprintf\fR command supports various format specifiers, which begin with a percent sign (%) and are
followed by one or more format characters. The most common format specifiers include:

.TP
.B %c
Print a character.

.TP
.B %s
Print a string.

.TP
.B %d, %i
Print a signed decimal integer.

.SH ARGUMENTS
\fIFORMAT\fR
A string that specifies the format of the output. It can contain plain text and format specifiers.

\fIARGUMENT\fR
Values to be formatted and printed according to the format specifiers in the \fIFORMAT\fR string.

.SH EXAMPLES
To print a simple string:

.BR printf "Hello, World!\n"

To print a formatted integer:

.BR printf "The answer is: %d\n" 42

.SH BUGS
Report bugs to https://github.com/Nathan9722/holbertonschool-printf

.SH AUTHOR
